    <h1>Hyderabadi Biryani</h1>
    <img src="https://images.openai.com/static-rsc-4/5el8IU0bHavi8gevXvC7RA9zjJDbVRRi5BawLVJY8x6rmosCIL-bdBwTGfxpGePxr2gRWdSudNs7QehgYCpTrbf67bWzEL-egDPyUtgqgXL6KEUVwHqogrddpNMCsyo_Dib0X8IwEJNODcZmKhAMBOeyNnqSOY1vfulgN1hf-5BCgTRM5rxUIa5b-CoUfG_m?purpose=fullsize" alt="Hyderabadi Biryani" width="540">
    <p>Aromatic and flavorful rice dish layered with spiced meat and cooked to perfection.</p>
    <h2>Ingredients:</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>500g chicken</li>
        <li>2 onions</li>
        <li>Yogurt</li>
        <li>Mint leaves</li>
        <li>Coriander leaves</li>
        <li>Biryani masala</li>
        <li>Saffron milk</li>
        <li>2 cups basmati rice</li>
<li>Ghee</li>
    </ul>
    <h2>Steps:</h2>
    <ol>
        <li>Fry onions until golden brown.</li>
        <li>Cook rice until 70% done.</li>
        <li>Layer marinated chicken, rice, fried onions, mint, and coriander.</li>
        <li>Add saffron milk and ghee.</li>
        <li>Cover tightly and cook on low flame (dum) for 30–40 minutes.</li>
        <li>Mix gently before serving.</li>
        <li>Serve with raita.</li>
        <li>Marinate chicken with yogurt and biryani masala.</li>
    </ol>
